All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Application
The Application class handles the Application object and holds Application (context), AppState (interface) and 6 concrete state classes.
Application.AppType
The possible categorized type of the application.
AppList
AppList maintains and manages a list of Applications.
AppManager
The AppManager class controls the creation and modification of applications and provides information to the GUI.
AppManagerGUI
Container for the ApplicationManager that has the menu options for new application files, loading existing files, saving files and quitting.
AppReader
Manages file input and reading/processing for a given Application file.
AppWriter
Handles Application file output and writing to a specific file.
Command
The Command class handles user actions and transitions causing the update of Application's state.
Command.CommandValue
Enumeration representing one of the four possible commands a user can make for the Application Manager FSM.
Command.Resolution
Enumeration representing the four possible ways a user can resolve an application.
